women/game-detail/518709\n}}\n\n==Qualified teams for FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup==\nThe following three teams from CONCACAF qualified for the [[2020 FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Team\n! Qualified on\n! data-sort-type=\"number\"|Previous appearances in [[FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup]]<sup>'''[[#1|1]]'''</sup>\n|-\n| <!--{{fbwu|17|}}-->TBD || <!--{{dts|2020|||addkey=1|format=dmy}}--> ||\n|-\n| <!--{{fbwu|17|}}-->TBD || <!--{{dts|2020|||addkey=2|format=dmy}}--> ||\n|-\n| <!--{{fbwu|17|}}-->TBD || <!--{{dts|2020|||format=dmy}}--> ||\n|}\n:<div id=\"1\"><sup>1</sup> '''Bold''' indicates champions for that year. ''Italic'' indicates hosts for that year.</div>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.concacaf.com/en/under-17s-women Concacaf Women's Under-17 Championship], CONCACAF.com\n\n{{CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Concacaf Women's U-17 Championship 2020}}\n[[Category:2020 CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship| ]]\n[[Category:CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship|2020]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 in CONCACAF football|Women's U-17 Championship]]\n[[Category:2020 in women's association football]]\n[[Category:2020 in youth association football]]\n[[Category:2020 FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup qualification]]\n[[Category:International association football competitions hosted by Mexico]]\n<!--[[Category:April 2020 sports events in Mexico]]\n[[Category:May 2020 sports events in Mexico]]-->\n[[Category:Scheduled association football competitions]]\n[[Category:Sports events postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox international football competition\n| tourney_name = CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship\n| year = 2020\n| other_titles = <!--Tournament name in native language of hosts-->\n| image =\n| size = 250px\n| country = Mexico\n| city =\n| dates = Postponed<br />(originally 18 April \u2013 3 May 2020)\n| num_teams = 20\n| confederations = 1\n| venues = TBC\n| cities = 1\n| champion_other = <!--{{fbwu|17|}}-->\n| count =\n| second_other = <!--{{fbwu|17|}}-->\n| third_other = <!--{{fbwu|17|}}-->\n| fourth_other = <!--{{fbwu|17|}}-->\n| matches =\n| goals =\n| attendance =\n| top_scorer =\n| player =\n| goalkeeper =\n| fair_play =\n| prevseason = [[2018 CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship|2018]]\n| nextseason = [[2022 CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship|2022]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2020 CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship''' will be the 7th edition of the [[CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship]], the biennial international youth [[association football|football]] championship organised by [[CONCACAF]] for the women's under-17 national teams of the North, Central American and Caribbean region. The tournament was originally scheduled to be held in [[Mexico]] between 18 April and 3 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.concacaf.com/en/under-17s-women/article/mexico-named-host-for-2020-concacaf-women-s-under-17-championship|title=Mexico Named Host for 2020 Concacaf Women's Under-17 Championship|publisher=CONCACAF.com|date=31 January 2020}}</ref> However on 19 March 2020, CONCACAF announced the decision to postpone the tournament due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]], with the new dates of the tournament to be confirmed later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.concacaf.com/en/article/concacaf-statement-on-additional-tournament-suspensions|title=Concacaf Statement on Additional Tournament Suspensions|publisher=CONCACAF|date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe final tournament is expanded from eight to 20 teams, using the same format as the [[2019 CONCACAF U-17 Championship]]. The top three teams of the tournament will qualify for the [[2020 FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup]] in [[India]] as the CONCACAF representatives.\n\n[[United States women's national under-17 soccer team|United States]] are the defending champions.\n\n==Qualified teams==\n{{Details|2020 CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship qualifying stage}}\n\nThe qualifying format has changed since the 2018 edition, and the teams are no longer divided into regional zones.\n\nThe 41 [[CONCACAF]] teams were ranked based on the CONCACAF Women\u2019s Under-17 Ranking as of 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.concacaf.com/en/rankings/womens-under-17|title=Concacaf Women's Under-17 Ranking|publisher=CONCACAF.com}}</ref> A total of 32 teams entered the tournament. The highest-ranked 16 entrants were exempt from qualifying and advanced directly to the group stage of the final tournament, while the lowest-ranked 16 entrants had to participate in the qualifying stage, where the four group winners advanced to the round of 16 of the knockout stage of the final tournament.<ref name=\"draw\">{{cite web|url=https://www.concacaf.com/en/under-17s-women/article/concacaf-announces-details-for-the-2020-concacaf-women-s-under-17-championship|title=Concacaf Announces Details for the 2020 Concacaf Women's Under-17 Championship|publisher=CONCACAF.com|date=8 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Round\n!width=200px| Team\n!width=180px| Qualification\n!width=120px data-sort-type=\"number\"| Appearance\n!width=320px| Previous best performance\n!width=100px| Previous [[FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup]] appearances\n|-\n|align=center rowspan=16| Group stage\n|align=left| {{fbwu|17|MEX}} <small>(hosts)</small>\n|align=center| {{sort|01|[[2020 CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship qualifying stage#Teams|1st ranked]] entrant}}\n|align=center|\n|align=center|\n|align=center| 5\n|-\n|align=left| {{fbwu|17|CAN}}\n|align=center| {{sort|02|[[2020 CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship qualifying stage#Teams|2nd ranked]] entrant}}\n|align=center|\n|align=center|\n|align=center| 6\n|-\n|align=left| {{fbwu|17|USA}} <small>([[2018 CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship|title holders]])</small>\n|align=center| {{sort|03|[[2020 CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship qualifying stage#Teams|3rd ranked]] entrant}}\n|align=center|\n|align=center|\n|align=center| 