eason-cut-to-17-games-call-delayed-on-r1-start|title=Season cut to 17 games, call delayed on R1 start|date=16 March 2020|accessdate=16 March 2020|publisher=Australian Football League|author=Mitch Cleary}}</ref>\n\nHowever, on 22 March 2020 the season was paused after the completion of Round 1 until 31 May 2020. This was a result of various Australian state governments announcing the closure of their borders due to the coronavirus.<ref name=\"AFL22Mar\"/>\n\n===Round 1===\n{{AFLGameHeader|title=Round 1 (Opening Round)}}\n{{AFLGame|Thursday, 19 March (7:40&nbsp;pm)|{{AFL Ric}}|16.9 (105)|H|{{AFL Car}}|12.9 (81)|[[Melbourne Cricket Ground|MCG]]|0|[https://www.afl.com.au/matches/2214#match-report Report]}}\n{{AFLGame|Friday, 20 March (7:50&nbsp;pm)|{{AFL WB}}|5.4 (34)|A|{{AFL Col}}|13.8 (86)|[[Docklands Stadium|Marvel Stadium]]|0|[https://www.afl.com.au/matches/2009#match-report Report]}}\n{{AFLGame|Saturday, 21 March (2:10&nbsp;pm)|{{AFL Ess}}|9.9 (63)|H|{{AFL Fre}}|8.9 (57)|[[Docklands Stadium|Marvel Stadium]]|0|<!--[ Report]-->}}\n{{AFLGame|Saturday, 21 March (4:05&nbsp;pm)|{{AFL Ade}}|11.5 (71)|A|{{AFL Syd}}|11.8 (74)|[[Adelaide Oval]]|0|<!--[ Report]-->}}\n{{AFLGame|Saturday, 21 March (7:40&nbsp;pm)|{{AFL GWS}}|17.3 (105)|H|{{AFL Gee}}|11.7 (73)|[[Sydney Showground Stadium|GIANTS Stadium]]|0|<!--[ Report]-->}}\n{{AFLGame|Saturday, 21 March (6:40&nbsp;pm)|{{AFL GC}}|4.5 (29)|A|{{AFL Por}}|10.16 (76)|[[Carrara Stadium|Metricon Stadium]]|0|<!--[ Report]-->}}\n{{AFLGame|Sunday, 22 March (1:05&nbsp;pm)|{{AFL NM}}|8.8 (56)|H|{{AFL StK}}|7.12 (54)|[[Docklands Stadium|Marvel Stadium]]|0|<!--[ Report]-->}}\n{{AFLGame|Sunday, 22 March (3:35&nbsp;pm)|{{AFL Haw}}|14.6 (90)|H|{{AFL BL}}|9.8 (62)|[[Melbourne Cricket Ground|MCG]]|0|<!--[ Report]-->}}\n{{AFLGame|Sunday, 22 March (3:40&nbsp;pm)|{{AFL WCE}}|12.6 (78)|H|{{AFL Mel}}|7.9 (51)|[[Perth Stadium|Optus Stadium]]|0|<!--[ Report]-->}}\n{{AFLGameFooter|notes=\n* {{AFL GWS}} scored at 85% accuracy, beating its previous highest 