ited-in-2020|title=Hawthorn Leaders United in 2020|publisher=[[Telstra Media]]|work=[[Hawthorn Football Club|Hawthorn]]|date=6 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{AFL Mel}}\n| [[Simon Goodwin]]\n| [[Max Gawn]]\n| [[Jack Viney]]\n| \n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.melbournefc.com.au/news/567573|title=Gawn named captain for 2020|publisher=[[Telstra Media]]|work=[[Melbourne Football Club|Melbourne]]|date=24 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{AFL Nor}}\n| [[Rhyce Shaw]]\n| [[Jack Ziebell]]\n| [[Shaun Higgins]], [[Robbie Tarrant]]\n| [[Ben Cunnington (footballer)|Ben Cunnington]], [[Trent Dumont]], [[Jamie Macmillan]], [[Jasper Pittard]], [[Jy Simpkin]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nmfc.com.au/news/560816/north-s-new-leadership-group|title=North's new leadership group|publisher=[[Telstra Media]]|work=[[North Melbourne Football Club|North Melbourne]]|date=6 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{AFL Por}}\n| [[Ken Hinkley]]\n| [[Tom Jonas]]\n| [[Hamish Hartlett]], [[Ollie Wines]]\n| \n|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.news.com.au/sport/afl/port-adelaide-do-away-with-cocaptaincy-model-after-one-season/news-story/096fc6ceca137b38227ed4dfb472e533|title=Port Adelaide do away with co-captaincy model after one season|author=AAP|website=[[News.com.au]]|date=6 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{AFL Ric}}\n| [[Damien Hardwick]]\n| [[Trent Cotchin]]\n| [[Jack Riewoldt]]\n| \n| <ref>{{cite web |title=Cotchin to captain in 2020 |url=https://www.richmondfc.com.au/news/576092/cotchin-to-captain-in-2020 |website=richmondfc.com.au |publisher=Telstra Media |accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{AFL StK}}\n| [[Brett Ratten]]\n| [[Jarryn Geary]]\n| [[Sebastian Ross]]\n| [[Jack Billings]], [[Bradley Hill (footballer)|Bradley Hill]], [[Tim Membrey]], [[Dylan Roberton]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title= Geary to captain Saints in 2020 |url=https://www.saints.com.au/news/565284/ |work=[[St Kilda Football Club|St Kilda]] |publisher=[[Telstra Media]] |date=19 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{AFL Syd}}\n| [[John Longmire]]\n| [[Josh Kennedy (footballer, born 1988)|Josh Kennedy]]<br/>[[Luke Parker (footballer)|Luke Parker]]<br/>[[Dane Rampe]]\n| \n| [[Lance Franklin]], [[Callum Mills]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sydneyswans.com.au/news/550334/leadership-group-locked-in|title=Leadership group locked in|publisher=[[Telstra Media]]|website=[[Sydney Swans]]|date=18 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{AFL WC}}\n| [[Adam Simpson]]\n| [[Luke Shuey]]\n| [[Josh Kennedy (footballer, born 1987)|Josh Kennedy]], [[Jeremy McGovern]]\n| [[Jack Darling]], [[Andrew Gaff]], [[Nic Naitanui]], [[Elliot Yeo]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |last1=Schmook |first1=Nathan |title=Gun Eagles join leadership group, Hurn steps away |url=https://www.afl.com.au/news/381561/gun-eagles-join-leadership-group-hurn-steps-away |website=westcoasteagles.com.au |publisher=Telstra Media |accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{AFL WB}}\n| [[Luke Beveridge]]\n| [[Marcus Bontempelli]]\n| [[Lachie Hunter]]\n| [[Josh Dunkley]], [[Jason Johannisen]], [[Mitch Wallis]], [[Easton Wood]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/afl/western-bulldogs-announce-marcus-bontempelli-as-new-captain-after-easton-wood-steps-down/news-story/46b534ab66ca2387f2ac61eb046e3881|title=Western Bulldogs announce Marcus Bontempelli as new captain after Easton Wood steps down|first=Josh|last=Gabelich|publisher=[[Fox Sports (Australia)|Fox Sports]]|date=10 December 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Coach changes==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:left;\"\n|- style=\"background:#C1D8FF;\"\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12em\"| Coach\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12em\"| Club\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12em\"| Date\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30em\"| Notes\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12em\"| Caretaker\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12em\"| New coach\n|-\n| {{sortname|John|Worsfold}}\n| {{AFL Ess}}\n| {{sort|2019-9-17|17 September 2019}}\n| Will step down at the conclusion of the club's 2020 season as part of a succession plan.<ref name=\"EssendonCoachChange\">{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/afl/afl-2019-essendons-succession-plan-john-worsfold-ben-rutten-john-worsfolds-family-in-perth/news-story/bbfbab84984746a50da0691c70781658|title=Essendon coach John Worsfold's beautiful tribute to 'selfless' family|publisher=Fox Sports Australia|first=Sarah|last=Olle|date=17 September 2019|accessdate=25 September 2019}}</ref>\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{sortname|Ben|Rutten}}<ref name=\"EssendonCoachChange\"/>\n|}\n\n==Post-season==\n===International Rules Series===\n{{Main|2020 International Rules Series}}\n\nThe [[International Rules Series]] is scheduled to return for the first time since 2017, with Australia agreeing to tour Ireland for a two-test series in mid-November.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/nov/19/afl-confirm-return-of-international-rules-series-in-2020-after-three-year-absence|title=AFL confirm return of International Rules Series in 2020 after three-year absence|author=Australian Associated Press|work=The Guardian|date=19 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{AFLGameHeader|title=2020 International Rules Series}}\n{{AFLGame|Sunday, 15 November (TBC)|[[Ireland international rules football team|Ireland]]||V|[[Australia international rules football team|Australia]]||TBC||}}\n{{AFLGame|Saturday, 21 November (TBC)|[[Ireland international rules football team|Ireland]]||V|[[Australia international rules football team|Australia]]||TBC||||}}\n{{AFLGameFooter|notes=}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{2020 AFL season}}\n{{Australian Football League}}\n\n[[Category:Australian Football League seasons]]\n[[Category:2020 Australian Football League season]]\n[[Category:2020 in Australian rules football]]\n[[Category:Sports events postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|AFL season 2020]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePremiership season:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: However  \u2192 However, , seventeen round \u2192 