{"title_page": "Boris Mordukhovich", "text_new": "'''Boris Mordukhovich''' is an [[Americans|American]] [[mathematician]] recognized for his research in the areas of [[Nonlinear functional analysis|nonlinear analysis]], [[Optimization (mathematics)|optimization]], and [[control theory]]. Mordukhovich is one of the founders of modern [[variational analysis]] and generalized differentiation.  Currently he is Distinguished University Professor and Lifetime Scholar of the Academy of Scholars at [[Wayne State University]] (Vice President, 2009-2010 and President, 2010-2011).\n\n==Life and works==\nMordukhovich was born and educated in the [[Soviet Union]]; he immigrated to the United States with his family in December 1988. He developed constructions of generalized differentiation (bearing now his name), and their development and applications to classes of problems in variational analysis, optimization, equilibrium, control, economics, engineering, and other fields.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Henrion |first1=R. |last2=Kruger |first2=A. |last3=Outrata |first3=J. |year=2008 |title=Boris Mordukhovich, The Never Tired Traveller, Celebrates His Sixtieth Birthday |url=http://140.127.138.68:88/w2c/isvao/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=32&Itemid=51 |journal=Set-Valued Analysis |volume=16 |issue= 2\u20133|pages=125\u2013127 |doi=10.1007/s11228-008-0069-9 }}{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Torres |first1=D. F. M. |last2=Zaslavski |first2=A. J. |year=2009 |title=Editorial to the special issue of the International Journal of Mathematics and Statistics (IJMS), dedicated to Boris S. Mordukhovich on the occasion of his 60th birthday |url=http://srv-ceoc.mat.ua.pt/ojs/index.php/ijms/article/viewFile/147/58 |journal=International Journal of Mathematics and Statistics|volume=5 |issue= |page=A09 }}{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>''Vietnam Journal of Mathematics'' Volume 42,Issue 4, https://link.springer.com/journal/10013/42/4?wt_mc=alerts.TOCjournals</ref> His theory and various applications have been summarized in the 2-volume monograph,<ref>B. S. Mordukhovich, \"''Variational Analysis and Generalized Differentiation, '''I''': Basic Theory, '''II''': Applications'',\" Grundlehren Series (Fundamental Principles of Mathematical Sciences), Vols. 330 and 331, Springer, 2006.</ref> and in the recent book.<ref>B. S. Mordukhovich, \"''Variational Analysis and Applications'',\" Springer Monographs in Mathematics, 2018.</ref> Mordukhovich has published more than 450 journal papers.\n\nMordukhovich is an AMS Fellow of the Inaugural Class,<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.ams.org/profession/ams-fellows/ams-fellows | title=American Mathematical Society}}</ref><ref>[http://www.ams.org/profession/fellows-list List of Fellows of the American Mathematical Society], retrieved 2013-02-10.</ref> a SIAM Fellow,<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://fellows.siam.org/index.php?sort=year&value=2011 | title=Fellows Program &#124; SIAM}}</ref> and a recipient of many international awards and honors, including [[Dr. Honoris Causa]] from the [[National Sun Yat-sen University]] in [[Taiwan]], [[University of Messina]],<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.tempostretto.it/news/riconoscimenti-accademici-laurea-magistrale-honoris-causa-matematica-boris-mordukhovich.html | title=Laurea magistrale honoris causa in Matematica a Boris Mordukhovich| date=2011-06-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.tempostretto.it/news/laurea-honoris-causa-universit-messina-insignisce-matematico-mordukhovich.html | title=L'Universit\u00e0 di Messina insignisce il matematico Mordukhovich| date=2011-06-17}}</ref> [[University of Alicante]] in [[Spain]],<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.ua.es/es/servicios/comunicacion/notas/08073003.html | title=La Primat\u00f3loga Inglesa Jane Goodall Ser\u00e1 Investida Doctora Honoris Causa Por la Universidad de Alicante}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ua.es/dossierprensa/2009/01/29/11.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-01-30 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716153315/http://www.ua.es/dossierprensa/2009/01/29/11.html |archivedate=2011-07-16 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ua.es/dossierprensa/2009/01/29/7.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-01-30 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716153324/http://www.ua.es/dossierprensa/2009/01/29/7.html |archivedate=2011-07-16 }}</ref> [[Babe\u0219-Bolyai University, Romania]]<ref>[[Babe\u0219-Bolyai University]]</ref>  and from [[Vietnam Academy of Science and Technology]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.vast.ac.vn | title=Vi\u1ec7n H\u00e0n l\u00e2m Khoa h\u1ecdc v\u00e0 C\u00f4ng ngh\u1ec7 Vi\u1ec7t Nam}}</ref> He is the Founding Editor (2008) and was a co-Editor-in-Chief (2009-2014) of ''[https://www.springer.com/math/analysis/journal/11228 Set-Valued and Variational Analysis],'' an international journal. Since 2016, he is a co-Editor-in-Chief, Applied Analysis and Optimization. He was Chair (2012 - 2015) of the International Working Group on Generalized Convexity and Monotonicity.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.genconv.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=86:10th-international-symposium-on-generalized-convexity-and-generalized-monotonicity&catid=1:latest-news | title=Working Group on Generalized Convexity}}</ref> In 2016, he was elected to the Accademia Peloritana dei Pericolanti (Italy). He is in the list of Highly Cited Researchers in Mathematics.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://community.thomsonreuters.com/t5/InCites-Customer-Forum/Preliminary-publication-of-new-lists-of-Highly-Cited-Researchers/td-p/36685 | title=Preliminary publication of new lists of Highly Cited Researchers| date=2012-12-31}}</ref>\n\n==External links==\n* [http://math.wayne.edu/~boris Boris Mordukhovich's Home Page]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n*{{MathGenealogy|id=39405}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mordukhovich, Boris}}\n[[Category:Mathematical analysts]]\n[[Category:Functional analysts]]\n[[Category:20th-century American mathematicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American mathematicians]]\n[[Category:Soviet mathematicians]] <!-- B-R??? -->\n[[Category:Wayne State University faculty]]\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Variational analysts]]\n[[Category:American people of Russian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Society for Industrial and Applied Mathematics]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the American Mathematical Society]]\n", "text_old": "'''Boris Mordukhovich''' is an [[Americans|American]] [[mathematician]] recognized for his research in the areas of [[Nonlinear functional analysis|nonlinear analysis]], [[Optimization (mathematics)|optimization]], and [[control theory]]. Mordukhovich is one of the founders of modern [[variational analysis]] and generalized differentiation.  Currently he is Distinguished University Professor and Lifetime Scholar of the Academy of Scholars at [[Wayne State University]] (Vice President, 2009-2010 and President, 2010-2011).\n\n==Life and works==\nMordukhovich was born and educated in the [[Soviet Union]]; he immigrated to the United States with his family in December 1988. He developed constructions of generalized differentiation (bearing now his name), and their development and applications to classes of problems in variational analysis, optimization, equilibrium, control, economics, engineering, and other fields.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Henrion |first1=R. |last2=Kruger |first2=A. |last3=Outrata |first3=J. |year=2008 |title=Boris Mordukhovich, The Never Tired Traveller, Celebrates His Sixtieth Birthday |url=http://140.127.138.68:88/w2c/isvao/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=32&Itemid=51 |journal=Set-Valued Analysis |volume=16 |issue= 2\u20133|pages=125\u2013127 |doi=10.1007/s11228-008-0069-9 }}{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Torres |first1=D. F. M. |last2=Zaslavski |first2=A. J. |year=2009 |title=Editorial to the special issue of the International Journal of Mathematics and Statistics (IJMS), dedicated to Boris S. Mordukhovich on the occasion of his 60th birthday |url=http://srv-ceoc.mat.ua.pt/ojs/index.php/ijms/article/viewFile/147/58 |journal=International Journal of Mathematics and Statistics|volume=5 |issue= |page=A09 }}{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>''Vietnam Journal of Mathematics'' Volume 42,Issue 4, https://link.springer.com/journal/10013/42/4?wt_mc=alerts.TOCjournals</ref> His theory and various applications have been summarized in the 2-volume monograph,<ref>B. S. Mordukhovich, \"''Variational Analysis and Generalized Differentiation, '''I''': Basic Theory, '''II''': Applications'',\" Grundlehren Series (Fundamental Principles of Mathematical Sciences), Vols. 330 and 331, Springer, 2006.</ref> and in the recent book.<ref>B. S. Mordukhovich, \"''Variational Analysis and Applications'',\" Springer Monographs in Mathematics, 2018.</ref> Mordukhovich has published more than 400 journal papers.\n\nMordukhovich is an AMS Fellow of the Inaugural Class,<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.ams.org/profession/ams-fellows/ams-fellows | title=American Mathematical Society}}</ref><ref>[http://www.ams.org/profession/fellows-list List of Fellows of the American Mathematical Society], retrieved 2013-02-10.</ref> a SIAM Fellow,<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://fellows.siam.org/index.php?sort=year&value=2011 | title=Fellows Program &#124; SIAM}}</ref> and a recipient of many international awards and honors, including [[Dr. Honoris Causa]] from the [[National Sun Yat-sen University]] in [[Taiwan]], [[University of Messina]],<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.tempostretto.it/news/riconoscimenti-accademici-laurea-magistrale-honoris-causa-matematica-boris-mordukhovich.html | title=Laurea magistrale honoris causa in Matematica a Boris Mordukhovich| date=2011-06-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.tempostretto.it/news/laurea-honoris-causa-universit-messina-insignisce-matematico-mordukhovich.html | title=L'Universit\u00e0 di Messina insignisce il matematico Mordukhovich| date=2011-06-17}}</ref> [[University of Alicante]] in [[Spain]],<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.ua.es/es/servicios/comunicacion/notas/08073003.html | title=La Primat\u00f3loga Inglesa Jane Goodall Ser\u00e1 Investida Doctora Honoris Causa Por la Universidad de Alicante}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ua.es/dossierprensa/2009/01/29/11.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-01-30 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716153315/http://www.ua.es/dossierprensa/2009/01/29/11.html |archivedate=2011-07-16 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ua.es/dossierprensa/2009/01/29/7.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-01-30 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716153324/http://www.ua.es/dossierprensa/2009/01/29/7.html |archivedate=2011-07-16 }}</ref> [[Babe\u0219-Bolyai University, Romania]]<ref>[[Babe\u0219-Bolyai University]]</ref>  and from [[Vietnam Academy of Science and Technology]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.vast.ac.vn | title=Vi\u1ec7n H\u00e0n l\u00e2m Khoa h\u1ecdc v\u00e0 C\u00f4ng ngh\u1ec7 Vi\u1ec7t Nam}}</ref> He is the Founding Editor (2008) and was a co-Editor-in-Chief (2009-2014) of ''[https://www.springer.com/math/analysis/journal/11228 Set-Valued and Variational Analysis],'' an international journal. Since 2016, he is a co-Editor-in-Chief, Applied Analysis and Optimization. He was Chair (2012 - 2015) of the International Working Group on Generalized Convexity and Monotonicity.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.genconv.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=86:10th-international-symposium-on-generalized-convexity-and-generalized-monotonicity&catid=1:latest-news | title=Working Group on Generalized Convexity}}</ref> In 2016, he was elected to the Accademia Peloritana dei Pericolanti (Italy). He is in the list of Highly Cited Researchers in Mathematics.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://community.thomsonreuters.com/t5/InCites-Customer-Forum/Preliminary-publication-of-new-lists-of-Highly-Cited-Researchers/td-p/36685 | title=Preliminary publication of new lists of Highly Cited Researchers| date=2012-12-31}}</ref>\n\n==External links==\n* [http://math.wayne.edu/~boris Boris Mordukhovich's Home Page]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n*{{MathGenealogy|id=39405}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mordukhovich, Boris}}\n[[Category:Mathematical analysts]]\n[[Category:Functional analysts]]\n[[Category:20th-century American mathematicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American mathematicians]]\n[[Category:Soviet mathematicians]] <!-- B-R??? -->\n[[Category:Wayne State University faculty]]\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Variational analysts]]\n[[Category:American people of Russian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Society for Industrial and Applied Mathematics]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the American Mathematical Society]]\n", "name_user": "Poetryandmath", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boris_Mordukhovich"}
{"title_page": "Thomas Edgar (MP)", "text_new": "{{short description|16th-century English politician}}\n{{For|other people named Thomas Edgar|Thomas Edgar (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2015}}\n\n'''Thomas Edgar''' (by 1508\u20131547), of [[Blewbury]], Berkshire; [[Bermondsey]], Surrey and London, was an English politician.\n\nHe was a [[Member of Parliament|Member]] (MP) of the [[Parliament of England]] for [[Malmesbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Malmesbury]] in 1529.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1509-1558/member/edgar-thomas-1508-47|title=EDGAR, Thomas (by 1508-47), of Blewbury, Berks.; Bermondsey, Surr. and London. - History of Parliament Online|website=Historyofparliamentonline.org|accessdate=3 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Edgar, Thomas}}\n[[Category:1547 deaths]]\n[[Category:People of the Tudor period]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1529\u20131536]]\n[[Category:Year of birth uncertain]]\n[[Category:People from Blewbury]]\n[[Category:People from Bermondsey]]\n\n{{England-pre1707-MP-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|16th-century English politician}}\n{{For|other people named Thomas Edgar|Thomas Edgar (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2015}}\n\n'''Thomas Edgar''' (by 1508\u20131547), of [[Blewbury]], Berkshire; [[Bermondsey]], Surrey and London, was an English politician.\n\nHe was a [[Member of Parliament|Member]] (MP) of the [[Parliament of England]] for [[Malmesbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Malmesbury]] in 1529.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1509-1558/member/edgar-thomas-1508-47|title=EDGAR, Thomas (by 1508-47), of Blewbury, Berks.; Bermondsey, Surr. and London. - History of Parliament Online|website=Historyofparliamentonline.org|accessdate=3 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Edgar, Thomas}}\n[[Category:1547 deaths]]\n[[Category:People of the Tudor period]]\n[[Category:English MPs 1529\u20131536]]\n[[Category:Year of birth uncertain]]\n\n\n{{England-pre1707-MP-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Verica Atrebatum", "label": "safe", "comment": "cats", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Edgar_(MP)"}
{"title_page": "Encyclopaedia of the Qur\u02be\u0101n", "text_new": "{{italic title}}\nThe '''''Encyclopaedia of the Qur\u02be\u0101n''''' (abbreviated '''EQ''') is an  [[encyclopedia]] dedicated to [[Qur'anic Studies]] published by [[Brill Publishers]].<ref>Promotion text by Brill:\n\"Drawing upon a rich scholarly heritage, Brill's Encyclopaedia of the Qur'\u0101n (EQ) combines alphabetically arranged articles about the contents of the Qur'\u0101n. It is an encyclopaedic dictionary of qur'\u0101nic terms, concepts, personalities, place names, cultural history and exegesis extended with essays on the most important themes and subjects within qur'\u0101nic studies.\" [http://www.brill.nl/encyclopaedia-quran-set-volumes-1-5-plus-index-volume ''Encyclopaedia of the Qur'an'' at Brill publishers]</ref></blockquote>\n\nIt was published in five volumes, edited by [[Jane Dammen McAuliffe]] et al. during 2001-2006 ({{ISBN|90-04-14743-8}}):\n* Vol. I: A-D (publication year 2001)\n* Vol. II: E-I (2002)\n* Vol. III: J-O (2003)\n* Vol. IV: P-Sh (2004)\n* Vol. V: Si-Z (2006)\n* Index Vol. (2006)\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Encyclopaedia of Islam]]\n* [[Encyclopaedia Iranica]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://referenceworks.brillonline.com/browse/encyclopaedia-of-the-quran Encyclopaedia of the Qur\u02be\u0101n] Online\n* Publisher site: [http://www.brill.nl/encyclopaedia-quran-set-volumes-1-5-plus-index-volume ''Encyclopaedia of the Qur'an'' at Brill publishers]\n* Review: {{cite journal |last=Iqbal|first=Muzaffar|authorlink=Muzaffar Iqbal |year=2008 |title=The Qur\u02be\u0101n, orientalism and the Encyclopaedia of the Qur\u02be\u0101n |journal=Journal of Qur'anic Research and Studies |volume=3 |issue=5 |location=Medina, Saudi Arabia |publisher=King Fahd Qur\u2019an Printing Complex |url=http://www.cis-ca.org/muzaffar/EQ-Rev.pdf }}\n* Another encyclopaedia: [http://iequran.com ''Integrated Encyclopedia of the Qur'an'' at IEQ project]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Encyclopaedia of the Qur'an}}\n[[Category:Encyclopedias of Islam|Qur'an, Encyclopaedia of]]\n[[Category:Non-Islamic Islam studies literature]]\n[[Category:Quranic studies]]\n[[Category:21st-century encyclopedias]]\n", "text_old": "{{italic title}}\nThe '''''Encyclopaedia of the Qur\u02be\u0101n''''' (abbreviated '''EQ''') is an  [[encyclopedia]] dedicated to the [[Qur'an]] published by [[Brill Publishers]].<ref>Promotion text by Brill:\n\"Drawing upon a rich scholarly heritage, Brill's Encyclopaedia of the Qur'\u0101n (EQ) combines alphabetically arranged articles about the contents of the Qur'\u0101n. It is an encyclopaedic dictionary of qur'\u0101nic terms, concepts, personalities, place names, cultural history and exegesis extended with essays on the most important themes and subjects within qur'\u0101nic studies.\" [http://www.brill.nl/encyclopaedia-quran-set-volumes-1-5-plus-index-volume ''Encyclopaedia of the Qur'an'' at Brill publishers]</ref></blockquote>\n\nIt was published in five volumes, edited by [[Jane Dammen McAuliffe]] et al. during 2001-2006 ({{ISBN|90-04-14743-8}}):\n* Vol. I: A-D (publication year 2001)\n* Vol. II: E-I (2002)\n* Vol. III: J-O (2003)\n* Vol. IV: P-Sh (2004)\n* Vol. V: Si-Z (2006)\n* Index Vol. (2006)\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Encyclopaedia of Islam]]\n* [[Encyclopaedia Iranica]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://referenceworks.brillonline.com/browse/encyclopaedia-of-the-quran Encyclopaedia of the Qur\u02be\u0101n] Online\n* Publisher site: [http://www.brill.nl/encyclopaedia-quran-set-volumes-1-5-plus-index-volume ''Encyclopaedia of the Qur'an'' at Brill publishers]\n* Review: {{cite journal |last=Iqbal|first=Muzaffar|authorlink=Muzaffar Iqbal |year=2008 |title=The Qur\u02be\u0101n, orientalism and the Encyclopaedia of the Qur\u02be\u0101n |journal=Journal of Qur'anic Research and Studies |volume=3 |issue=5 |location=Medina, Saudi Arabia |publisher=King Fahd Qur\u2019an Printing Complex |url=http://www.cis-ca.