{"title_page": "2020 OFC U-19 Championship", "text_new": "{{Infobox international football competition\n| tourney_name = OFC U-19 Championship\n| year = 2020\n| other_titles = <!--Name in native language of hosts-->\n| image = \n| size = 150px\n| country = Samoa\n| country2 = \n| dates = July 2020\n| num_teams = 11\n| confederations = 1\n| venues = TBC\n| cities = TBC\n| champion_other = <!--{{fbu|20|}}-->\n| count = \n| second_other = <!--{{fbu|20|}}-->\n| third_other = <!--{{fbu|20|}}-->\n| fourth_other = <!--{{fbu|20|}}-->\n| matches = \n| goals = \n| top_scorer = \n| player = \n| goalkeeper = \n| fair_play = \n| prevseason = [[2018 OFC U-19 Championship|2018]]\n| nextseason = [[2022 OFC U-19 Championship|2022]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2020 OFC U-19 Championship''' will be the 23rd edition of the [[OFC U-19 Championship|OFC U-19/U-20 Championship]], the biennial international youth [[association football|football]] championship organised by the [[Oceania Football Confederation]] (OFC) for the men's under-19/under-20 national teams of Oceania. The tournament will be held in the [[Samoa]] in July 2020.<ref>{{cite web |title=Hosts confirmed for 2020 Youth Tournaments |url=https://www.oceaniafootball.com/hosts-confirmed-for-2020-youth-tournaments/ |website=Oceania Football Confederation |accessdate=4 March 2020 |date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe top two teams of the tournament will qualify for the [[2021 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in [[Indonesia]] as the OFC representatives.\n\n[[New Zealand national under-20 football team|New Zealand]] are the two-time defending champions.\n\n==Teams==\nAll 11 [[FIFA]]-affiliated national teams from the [[Oceania Football Confederation|OFC]] are eligible to enter the tournament.\n\nStarting from this edition, male youth tournaments no longer have a four-team qualifying stage, and all teams compete in one tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oceaniafootball.com/ofc-mens-youth-tournaments-continue-to-evolve/|title=OFC male youth tournaments continue to evolve|publisher=Oceania Football Confederation|date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n''Note: All appearance statistics include those in the qualifying stage (2016 and 2018).''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n|-\n! Team\n! data-sort-type=\"number\"|Appearance\n! Previous best performance\n|-\n| {{fbu|20|ASA}} || 6th || {{sort|05|Group stage}} ([[1998 OFC U-20 Championship|1998]], [[2011 OFC U-20 Championship|2011]], [[2014 OFC U-20 Championship|2014]])\n|-\n| {{fbu|20|COK}} || 4th || {{sort|05|Group stage}} ([[2001 OFC U-20 Championship|2001]], [[2016 OFC U-20 Championship|2016]])\n|-\n| {{fbu|20|FIJ}} || 22nd || {{sort|01|'''Champions'''}} ([[2014 OFC U-20 Championship|2014]])\n|-\n| {{fbu|20|NCL}} || 13th || {{sort|02|Runners-up}} ([[2008 OFC U-20 Championship|2008]])\n|-\n| {{fbu|20|NZL}} || 22nd || {{sort|01|'''Champions'''}} ([[1980 OFC U-20 Championship|1980]], [[1992 OFC U-20 Championship|1992]], [[2007 OFC U-20 Championship|2007]], [[2011 OFC U-20 Championship|2011]], [[2013 OFC U-20 Championship|2013]], [[2016 OFC U-20 Championship|2016]], [[2018 OFC U-19 Championship|2018]])\n|-\n| {{fbu|20|PNG}} || 15th || {{sort|04|Fourth place}} ([[1978 OFC U-20 Championship|1978]], [[1982 OFC U-20 Championship|1982]])\n|-\n| {{fbu|20|SAM}} (hosts) || 10th || {{sort|05|Group stage}} ([[1988 OFC U-20 Championship|1988]], [[1994 OFC U-20 Championship|1994]], [[1998 OFC U-20 Championship|1998]], [[2001 OFC U-20 Championship|2001]], [[2002 OFC U-20 Championship|2002]], [[2005 OFC U-20 Championship|2005]], [[2007 OFC U-20 Championship|2007]])\n|-\n| {{fbu|20|SOL}} || 10th || {{sort|02|Runners-up}} ([[2005 OFC U-20 Championship|2005]], [[2011 OFC U-20 Championship|2011]])\n|-\n| {{fbu|20|TAH}} || 12th || {{sort|01|'''Champions'''}} ([[1974 OFC U-20 Championship|1974]], [[2008 OFC U-20 Championship|2008]])\n|-\n| {{fbu|20|TGA}} || 7th || {{sort|05|Group stage}} ([[1998 OFC U-20 Championship|1998]], [[2001 OFC U-20 Championship|2001]], [[2002